by carriage. I wouldn’t have it any other way. It allows me to fully experience the foreign culture and the Ukrainian hospitality. When I get off the carriage, I’m greeted by the local shop keepers that I’m friends with. Even after I moved a couple of kilometers down the road, I still feel connected to the store and people since I’m walking distance away.

God has placed me exactly where he wants me to be. It’s a good feeling to be where I’m at. Although I’ve only been in Ukraine 4 months, I grew to love the people so much. Even though we hardly know each other, it feels like we’re one big family. I love it so much that I don’t even consider leaving. If I could stay here forever, I would.

These people are so genuine with their affection for me. I can feel it in my bones. I want my life to be defined by God. I want my life to revolve around him and just continue to help people until my last breath.

I’m thinking about becoming a full time missionary. I wanna use all of my adult life to help, teach, and evangelize this world. I don’t care if it’s in my neighborhood or half way around the world. God has blessed me with everything he’s ever given me, so he deserves more than worship in a church. I wanna serve him with all my heart, all my lying, all my strength as I carry my cross.

I
